properties.headline: Flood Warning issued January 23 at 4:33PM PST until January 24 at 8:20PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in
Washington...

Stillaguamish River At Arlington affecting Snohomish County
Bogachiel River Near La Push affecting Clallam County
Skokomish River At Potlatch affecting Mason County
Satsop River Near Satsop affecting Grays Harbor County


Heavy rainfall will continue across Western Washington through tonight, with flooding continuing.

The Flood Warning continues for
The Satsop River Near Satsop
* Until Friday evening.
* At  4:15 PM Thursday the stage was 38.4 feet.
* Flood stage is 38.0 feet.
* Minor flooding is forecast to continue.
* Forecast...The river will continue to rise and crest near 38.8 feet
early Friday morning. The river will likely fall below flood stage Friday
late morning.
* Impact...At 38.0 feet, the Satsop River will flood low pasture lands
and some roads along the river.
properties.instruction:
Do not drive cars...vans...or trucks through flooded areas...this is
the cause of most flood related deaths in Washington. Be alert for
rapid changes and monitor developments by listening to NOAA Weather
radio or other local media.
